# CAIP-2 and CAIP-10 Standards

Use chain-agnostic identifiers per [CAIP-2](https://standards.chainagnostic.org/CAIPs/caip-2) and [CAIP-10](https://standards.chainagnostic.org/CAIPs/caip-10). **The reference format depends on the namespace—do not assume numeric chain IDs for all chains.**

## CAIP-2 (Blockchain ID)

Format: `namespace:reference`

- **namespace**: `[-a-z0-9]{3,8}`
- **reference**: `[-_a-zA-Z0-9]{1,32}` — semantics are namespace-specific

## CAIP-10 (Account ID)

Format: `chain_id:account_address`

- **chain_id**: Valid CAIP-2 string
- **account_address**: `[-.%a-zA-Z0-9]{1,128}` (chain-specific format)

## Namespace-Specific References

| Namespace | Reference Type                             | Examples                                                                             |
| --------- | ------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| eip155    | u64 chain ID                               | `eip155:1`, `eip155:42161`                                                           |
| solana    | First 32 chars of genesis hash (Base58btc) | `solana:5eykt4UsFv8P8NJdTREpY1vzqKqZKvdp`, `solana:EtWTRABZaYq6iMfeYKouRu166VU2xqa1` |
| starknet  | String identifier                          | `starknet:SN_MAIN`, `starknet:SN_GOERLI`                                             |
| sui       | Network name                               | `sui:mainnet`, `sui:testnet`, `sui:devnet`                                           |
| tvm       | Integer global_id                          | `tvm:42`, `tvm:-239`                                                                 |

## Correct vs Incorrect

```rust
// ❌ WRONG - numeric for Solana/Starknet
caip2: format!("solana:{}", chain_id),   // chain_id is u64
caip2: format!("starknet:{}", chain_id),

// ✅ CORRECT
caip2: format!("solana:{}", genesis_hash_32_chars),
caip2: format!("starknet:{}", "SN_MAIN"),
caip2: format!("eip155:{}", chain_id),
caip2: format!("sui:mainnet"),
caip2: format!("tvm:{}", global_id),
```

## Resolution Methods

- **Solana**: RPC `getGenesisHash`, truncate result to first 32 chars. See [Solana namespace](https://namespaces.chainagnostic.org/solana/caip2).
- **Starknet**: RPC `starknet_chainId`, decode hex to string (e.g. `SN_MAIN`). See [Starknet namespace](https://namespaces.chainagnostic.org/starknet/caip2).
- **Sui**: Use `mainnet`, `testnet`, or `devnet`; RPC `suix_getChainIdentifier` for verification. See [Sui namespace](https://namespaces.chainagnostic.org/sui/caip2).
- **TVM**: GraphQL `blocks.global_id` (integer). See [TVM namespace](https://namespaces.chainagnostic.org/tvm/caip2).
- **eip155**: Use numeric chain ID from EIP-155.
